UML:TaggedValue.value: Scope: This part of ISO 19152 provides the concepts and structure for standardization for georegulation in the marine space. This standard addresses the information structures related to management of legal spaces in the marine environment, such as the establishment of maritime limits and boundaries, marine fishery and resource management and rights and associated restrictions and responsibilities in the marine environment including the sea bottom, the surface and the water column. This part of 19152 establishes the common elements and basic schema that address the marine space. It builds upon the common components defined in 19152 Part 1 – Fundamentals, of obligations (rights, restrictions, responsibilities) with the specificity of having a geographical component (spatial unit) and related to a party or parties.

geometric compatibility constraint - Geometric types are restricted to point, multi-point (only for soundings), coverage (only for bathymetry and currents), curve (defined as a set of vertices and circular arc), surface and volume in 2 ½ dimensions in order to ensure alignment with IHO S-100.

This package contains the classes defined as part of the MG_Administrative section. Six classes and two code lists are defined. This section corresponds to the administrative package inherited from LADM part 1. In addition, the MG_Goverance class has been included to allow for the description of the context information from a proclamation, law or treaty document.

This package contains the classes defined as part of the MG_SpatialUnit section. Fifteen classes, eight code lists and one datatype are defined: MG_Party, MG_PartyMember, MG_PartyTypeList, and MG_GroupPartyTypeList. The Feature/Attribute Spatial Unit structure makes use of the feature structure from ISO 19109 and 19110 implementing the Spatial Unit identified in part 1. The structure defined her aligns with the geometry approach established in IHO S-100, including maintenance of the planar graph topological constraint.

This package contains the classes defined as part of the MG_Party section. Two classes and two code lists are defined: MG_Party, MG_PartyMember, MG_PartyTypeList, and MG_GroupPartyTypeList.

This package contains the classes defined as part of the MG_Source section. One class is defined: MG_Source. Sourcing is done by reference. No distinction is made between spatial and other sources because many sources, such as treaties, or laws define both spatial and other information.

correspondence constraint - There is a 1:1 correspondence between instances of the MG_SpatialAttribute and the corresponding instances of the MG_AdditionalSpatialInformation carrying additional information.

{multiplicity constraint - Only one Spatial Attribute Type version may be associated with one FeatureUnit instance at one time.}
{type constraint - All Spatial Attribute Types associated with a FeatureUnit shall be of the same geometric type point, curve or surface. }

A party is a person or organization or group . This class is realized from ISO 19152-1 LADM Fundamentals "LA_Party" and "LA_GroupParty" This class is a realization because it inherits from LA_Party, but it makes use of different code lists than LA_Party suited to the Marine Space. It is also a combination of both LA_Party and LA_Group Party. LA_GroupParty describes any number of parties, forming together a distinct entity, with each party registered. Since LA_GroupParty is a subtype of LA_Party this is described as a single class "MG_Party" that includes a conditional attribute "MG_partyGroupTypeList" that defines the type of a group party. This combined structure assists implementation.

The MG_RRR class is an abstract collection class allowing for the definition of Rights, Restrictions and/or Responsibilities. A subclass of LA_RRR is a "Right" (or social tenure relationship), a "Restriction", or a "Responsibility". This class and its subtypes are realized from LA_RRR as defined in 19152 -1. The RRR objects are information objects that carry an object identifier "Oid". They can be referenced as objects from the attributes associated with a Feature Object. This allows "Right", "Responsibility" and "Restrictions" to be re-used by several objects. That is, several objects may reference the same RRR objects. MG_RRR is an information object since it does not directly take on spatial attributes. An information object is a structure defined in IHO S-100.

This package contains the classes defined as part of the MG_SpatialUnit section. Fifteen classes, eight code lists and one datatype are defined: MG_Party, MG_PartyMember, MG_PartyTypeList, and MG_GroupPartyTypeList. The Feature/Attribute Spatial Unit structure makes use of the feature structure from ISO 19109 and 19110 implementing the Spatial Unit identified in part 1. The structure defined her aligns with the geometry approach established in IHO S-100, including maintenance of the planar graph topological constraint.

Item Type: Code List Value Domain: MG Associated Attribute: MG_JurisdictionDomainTypeList Name: seabedSurface Definition: Describes an the interface between the "waterColumn" and the "subsoil", submerged land surface found under the oceans. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: identical Remarks: Registered as a code list value in the IHO Geospatial Information Registry <https://registry.iho.int/> This code list value is particular to the MLB domain and is marked with a stereotype <MLB>.

Item Type: Code List Value Domain: MG Associated Attribute: MG_JurisdictionDomainTypeList Name: subsoil Definition: Describes a space below the "landSurface" and the "seabedSurface" . Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: identical Remarks: Registered as a code list value in the IHO Geospatial Information Registry <https://registry.iho.int/> This code list value is particular to the MLB domain and is marked with a stereotype <MLB>.

Item Type: Code List Value Domain: MG Associated Attribute: MG_JurisdictionDomainTypeList Name: waterColumn Definition: Describes a space from the "seabedSurface" up to the "waterSurface". Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: identical Remarks: Registered as a code list value in the IHO Geospatial Information Registry <https://registry.iho.int/> This code list value is particular to the MLB domain and is marked with a stereotype <MLB>.

Item Type: Code List Value Domain: MG Associated Attribute: MG_JurisdictionDomainTypeList Name: waterSurface Definition: Describe the interface between the "airspace" and "waterColumn". Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: identical Remarks: Registered as a code list value in the IHO Geospatial Information Registry <https://registry.iho.int/> This code list value is particular to the MLB domain and is marked with a stereotype <MLB>.

Domain: MG Name: MG_Point Definition: This component describes a spatial attribute that takes on point spatial geometry Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: generalized Remarks: Provides point spatial geometry for a Feature Unit in a consistent coordinate reference system. MG_Point spatial attributes have a consistent geometric description and coordinate reference system and may participate in a geometric complex. It may be processed in a GIS system.

Domain: MG Name: geometry Data Type: GM_Object = GM_Point Definition: This spatial attribute identifies the geometric primitive to be GM_Point. Remarks: This spatial attribute overwrites the attribute geometry in the abstract class MG_SpatialAttribute with the value "GM_Point", identifying point geometry as defined in ISO 19107 Spatial Schema. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-100 Part 7 Similarity to Source: identical

Item Type: Code List Domain: MG Name: MG_pointTypeList Code List Type: open enumeration Definition: This code list describes how the point was created. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: identical Remarks: The code list MG_PointTypeList plays the same role as the code list LA_PointType but is different to suite the Marine Space georegulation environment especially Marine Limits and Boundaries.

Item Type: Code List Value Domain: MG Associated Attribute: MG_PointTypeList Name: computed Definition: Describes a location that is computed in accordance with the definition described in the source through proper geodetic calculations. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: For example, the intersection of two arcs over an ellipsoidal surface. A point may be established to support construction computations. Registered as an attribute type in the IHO Geospatial Information Registry <https://registry.iho.int/>

Item Type: Code List Value Domain: MG Associated Attribute: MG_PointTypeList Name: defined Definition: Describes a "Location" that is derived from a legislative document or other definitive sources. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: Registered as an attribute type in the IHO Geospatial Information Registry <https://registry.iho.int/>

Domain: MG Name: locationReference Definition: This data type describes a point location. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: generalization Remarks: A point location is described as a string of text, even if it is numeric data, in exactly the same way that it is described in the source legal document. A reference system may be associated, although it is not necessarily available and may need to be inferred from the source document.

Domain: MG Name: referenceSystem Data Type: CRS Definition: The attribute "referenceSystem" allows a CoordinateReferencingSystem (CRS) to optionally be specified at the "MG_AdditionalSpatialInformation" level. Remarks: In many other geospatial data products the CRS is only defined at the metadata level and applies for the whole data set; however, in this part (part-3) it is necessary to detail it right down to the specific instances of geometry since treaty points and lines may come from different sources such as different treaties that may use different CRS. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as attribute value in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: generalized

Domain: MG Name: textualPosition Data Type: CharacterString Definition: This attribute defines a point coordinate value in a textual format, in exactly the same way that it is described in the source legal document. Remarks: This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute value in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: generalized

Domain: MG Name: MG_Volume_Attributes Definition: Additional attribute(s) that describe volume spatial geometry. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: generalized Remarks: Additional spatial information attributes provide information that augments volume spatial geometry.

Domain: MG Name: volumeVerticalExtent Data Type: Distance Definition: The vertical extent of a volume established as a distance measured against a vertical position reference point. Remarks: Vertical extent is given in the units established through units of measure. Vertical extent is given in the units established through "units of measure" (uom) defined for distance. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: restructured

Domain: MG Name: volumeVerticalPosition Data Type: GM_Point Definition: A reference point used to establish a bound for the vertical extent of a volume. Remarks: GM_Point geometry as per ISO 19107 Spatial Schema, defining a reference from which to measure vertical extent. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: restructured

This package contains the classes defined as part of the MG_Source section. One class is defined: MG_Source. Sourcing is done by reference. No distinction is made between spatial and other sources because many sources, such as treaties, or laws define both spatial and other information.

Domain: MG Name: MG_Source Definition: Descriptive documentation that supports, complement or describes the associated object. Reference: ISO 19152-1 Definition Source: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: Realized from ISO 19152-1 LADM "LA_Source". The "MG_Source" objects are shared attributes by reference.

Domain: MG Name: gID Data Type: CharacterString Definition: The Marine Resource Name (MRN) is an optional identifier in the marine space that is a permanent global identifier, allowing marine space management. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: generalization Remarks: IHO provides guidance on the structure of the MRN as a Globally Unique Identifier (GUID) based on the Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for those items undeer the jurisdiction of the IHO. The type of URI used by IHO is a Universal Resource Name (URN).

Domain: MG Name: sID Alias: sID per LA_Source Data Type: Oid Definition: This attribute is the identifier of the source. Reference: ISO 19152-1 Definition Source: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: This allows reference to "Source" information objects using the “Oid” (Object ID) attribute type. The “Oid” comprises a unique character string and a namespace identifier which is also a unique character string. An example might be "Source-9" where "Source" is the namespace identifier, "-" is a delimiter and "9" is the unique id within that namespace. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceAdministrativeDateStamp Alias: LA_Source: lifeSpanStamp Data Type: DateTime Definition: This attribute defines the moment that the event represented by the instance of "Source" is further processed. Reference: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: specialization, restructured and renamed Remarks: This is the moment of "endLifespan" of old instances, and the moment of "startLifespan" of new instances. This attribute has been renamed to fit the context of the marine space. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceAuthoritiveDate Alias: LA_Source: acceptance Data Type: DateTime Definition: This attribute defines the date of force of law of the "Source" by an authority. Reference: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: specialization restructured, renamed Remarks: This attribute has been renamed to fit the context of the marine space. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceAvailabilityStatus Alias: availabilityStatus per LA_Source Data Type: LA_AvailabilityStatusType Definition: This attribute defines the reference to the availability status of source document. Reference: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: restructured and renamed Remarks: This attribute has been renamed to fit the context of the marine space. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceDocumentName Alias: LA_Source: source Data Type: CharacterString Definition: Name of the document that defines the object - for example the document (legislation, treaty, title) Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: For simplicity the metadata CI_ResponsibilityParty structure referenced in LA_Source has been restructured to be a source reference in the style used in the legislative, treaty or other marine space environment represented as a character string. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceDocumentType Alias: LA_Source: maintype Data Type: CharacterString Definition: This attribute defines the type of source document Reference: ISO 19152-1; ISO 19115-1 Similarity to Source: generalized and renamed Remarks: This attribute has been renamed and generalized to fit the context of the marine space. The equivalent attribute from LA_Source takes its value from ISO 19115-1 metadata from the class CI_PresentationFormCode. This part of the ISO metadata standard is not included in IHO S_100 part 4 metadata. Therefore a free form character string is provided as the data type. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: Source External Archive Identifier Alias: LA_Source: extArchiveID Data Type: ExtArchive Definition: The identifier of a "Source" in an external registration, as per the description given in the class ExtArchive. Reference: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: restyled Remarks: The code list is taken directly for ISO 19152-1. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceOnlineResource Alias: Data Type: onlineResource Definition: URL - this is official the URL (or equivalent online resource) where the document is distributed. Reference: ISO 19115-1 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceQuality Alias: LA_Source: quality Data Type: DQ_Element Definition: The quality of the "Source". Reference: ISO 19152-1 Definition Source: ISO 19157 Similarity to Source:restyled Remarks: This attribute is inherited from LA_Source in part 1 of this document. The treatment of quality is now addressed in ISO 19157 as a "Quality Report" in a simpler manner to the set of quality attributes that previously were part of metadata. This approach is used because it is more general than the previous approach used in ISO 19115 and IHO S-100. The attribute values previously is inherited directly from ISO 19115 Metadata and IHO document. S-100 are given below for backward compatibility. The DQ_Element attributes are: "nameOfMeasure", "measureIdentification", "measureDescription", "evaluationMethodType", "evaluationMethodDescription", "evaluationProcedure", "dateTime", "result". This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceRecordation Alias: LA_Source: recordation CamelCase: sourceRecordation Data Type: DateTime Definition: The date of registration (recordation) of the "Source" by registering authority Reference: ISO 19152-1 Definition Source: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceRegistryNumber Data Type: CharacterString Definition: Unique official identifier of the record in a registry. Reference: IHO S-121 Definition Source: IHO S-121 Similarity to Source: restructured Remarks: For example, the identifier may follow the methodology in states with registers of legislative instruments. Document level versioning is controlled by the registry ID. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

Domain: MG Name: sourceSubmissionDate Alias: LA_Source: submission Data Type: DateTime Definition: This attribute defines the date of submission of the "Source" by a party. Reference: ISO 19152-1 Similarity to Source: restructured and renamed Remarks: This attribute has been renamed to fit the context of the marine space. This attribute is used in IHO S-121 and is registered as an attribute in the IHO register <https://registry.iho.int/> and as such can be expanded within the IHO process.

This diagram shows the overall structure of the Marine Space Georegulation spatial geometry. It shows the subtypes of MG_FeatureUnit and of MG_SpatialAttribute, and of MG_AdditionalSpatialInfo and the relationships between these subtypes.

A party is a person or organization that plays a role in rights. A Party is considered as an object which allows it to be shared. That is, a GroupParty may be composed out of other instances of MG_Party. The PartyMember class provides an attribute on the composition attribute that forms a group out of several party members. This optional attribute allows parties to have different shares within a group. The types of Parties and Group Parties are described by MG_PartyType and MG_PartyGroupType. This diagram shows the Party structure.

UML:Diagram.name: Fig 02 Marine Georegulation Application Schema Overview

UML:TaggedValue.value: This diagram shows the overall structure of the Marine Space Georegulation Application Schema. The four identified groups correspond to the packages inherited from LADM part 1 Fundamentals with the feature structure from ISO 19109 and 19110 implementing the Spatial Unit identified in part 1. In addition, the MG_Governance class has been included to augment the Administrative Group.

This diagram shows the inheritance of the Party structure from LA_ Party as defined in 19152-1. The structure of MG_Party has been simplified to assist in implementation; however, it is homomorphic with the LA_Party structure defined in 19152-1. Different codelists are used to support the Marine Georegulation (MG) environment. Because MG_Party uses different code lists and associations that LA_Party, a realization relationship is required. (If a subtyping relationship were used then the attributes and types from LA_Party would be inherited.)

This diagram shows the inheritance of the Administrative Section from the administrative package as defined in 19152-1 LADM part 1 Fundamentals. In addition, the MG_Goverance class has been included to allow for the description of the context information from a proclamation, law or treaty document. Because MG_BAUnit and MG_RRR uses different code lists and associations than the equivalent classes in 19152-1, a realization relationship is required. (If a subtyping relationship were used then the attributes and types would be inherited.)

This diagram shows the structure of the Marine Space Administrative Section Schema. This section corresponds to the administrative package inherited from LADM part 1. In addition, the MG_Goverance class has been included to allow for the description of the context information from a proclamation, law or treaty document.
This diagram shows the special data type classes Oid and Fraction that are used as data types within this model.

This diagram shows the relationships between the Party Section and the Administrative Section. There are two relationships, the primary being the rrrParty relationship where a party is associated with a Right, Restriction or Responsibility, and the other being the baunitAsParty relationship where an administrative unit can act as a party.
This diagram shows the Feature/Attribute Spatial Unit structure with the feature structure from ISO 19109 and 19110 implementing the Spatial Unit identified in part 1.
This diagram shows the package relationships within the overall ISO 19152-2 Marine Georegulation package part of the ISO 19152 LADM series.
